I"∏<h2 id="insert-raw-html-and-jekyll-code">Insert raw html and jekyll code</h2>

<p>to show contents, it‚Äôs essential to make us of Jekyll variables, like ‚Äúsite‚Äù, in html.</p>

<p>use a format as the following to list all posts:</p>

<div class="language-html highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="nt">&lt;ul&gt;</span>
  {% for post in site.posts %} 
    {% if post.categories contains 'quick_notes' %}
      <span class="nt">&lt;li&gt;</span>
        <span class="nt">&lt;a</span> <span class="na">href=</span><span class="s">""</span><span class="nt">&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span>
      <span class="nt">&lt;/li&gt;</span>
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}
<span class="nt">&lt;/ul&gt;</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>showing posts with the tag ‚Äúquick_notes‚Äù, and it will look like this:</p>

<ul>
  
    
  
    
  
    
      <li>
        <a href="/quick_notes/2020/11/20/welcome-to-jekyll.html">Jekyll welcome message</a>
      </li>
    
  
    
  
    
  
    
  
    
      <li>
        <a href="/quick_notes/2020/11/19/Content_creation.html">listing all posts</a>
      </li>
    
  
</ul>

